section*
  type procedure
  code $loinc#10185-7 Hospital discharge procedures Narrative
  title Significant Procedures
  text """Gastric lavage was performed on admission to remove ingested gastric contents, which were subsequently analysed for toxicological and microbiological pathogens. Intravenous hydration was maintained over the 48-hour admission. Discharge education was provided regarding peanut allergy awareness, recognition of hidden allergens in local and regional foods, and recommended emergency preparedness measures."""
