    status completed
section*
  type medication
  code $loinc#87232-5 Medication administration.brief
  title Medications
  text """No pharmacological treatment was required at discharge. Supportive IV fluid therapy was administered during admission only. Patient education was provided as the primary intervention."""
section*
  type careplan
  code $loinc#18776-5 Plan of care note
  title Follow-up and Care Plan
  text = """<ul><li>Allergy Management: Strict avoidance of all peanut-containing foods, including hidden sources in local and regional specialities</li><li>Emergency Preparedness: Recommendation to carry emergency antihistamines and/or an epinephrine auto-injector (EpiPen) at all times, especially when travelling abroad</li><li>Primary Care Follow-up: Appointment with GP or allergist upon return to Poland to review allergy management plan and consider formal allergy testing if not previously performed</li><li>Patient Education: Awareness of ingredient labelling, communication of allergy in restaurants (in local language if abroad), and recognition of early allergic symptoms</li><li>Dietary Caution: Particular vigilance with regional and traditional foods where allergens such as peanuts may not be visibly declared</li></ul>"""
  entry*
    type careplan
    date 2026-03-03
    category $sct#414285001 Allergy to peanuts (finding)
    code $sct#306206005 Referral to allergy service (procedure)
    activity* $sct#306206005 Referral to allergist on return home #not-started
    activity* $sct#182836005 Review of allergy management plan #not-started
    activity* $sct#409073007 Allergy education reinforcement #not-started